<item>
            <title>[SOLR-15691] Admin UI raises yellow warning even when only case of hostnames differ</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-15691</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Admin UI raises yellow warning &quot;Your ZK connection string (n hosts) is different from the dynamic ensemble config (n hosts).&quot; even when hostnames are only different by upder/lowercase.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Code for warning was introduced by&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-14371&quot; title=&quot;Zk StatusHandler should know about dynamic zk config&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-14371&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-14371&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Zk StatusHandler should know about dynamic zk config (&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/lucene-solr/pull/1392&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;#1392&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See solr/core/src/java/org/apache/solr/handler/admin/ZookeeperStatusHandler.java method getZkStatus(String zkHost)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Method creates 2 sorted List&amp;lt;String&amp;gt; (connStringHosts and dynamicHosts) to verify the difference via containsAll, but this should be made case insensitive (e.g. by mapping the hostnames to lowercase).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
